==English==

===Etymology===
The word comes from the {{etyl|la|en}} ''[[desquamare]]'' meaning "to scrape the scales off a fish."

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|medical|lang=en}} The [[shedding]] of the outer layers of the [[skin]]. For example, once the rash of  measles fades, there is desquamation.

